1
00:01:29,539 --> 00:01:34,940
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:37,670
[Episode 13]

3
00:01:41,759 --> 00:01:42,490
You're back.

4
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:54,690
Why are you smiling?

5
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:57,400
I'm reading.

6
00:01:57,590 --> 00:01:59,530
"High-Frequency Electronic Circuits."

7
00:01:59,530 --> 00:02:01,050
Is there a joke in that book?

8
00:02:01,050 --> 00:02:02,260
No, no.

9
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:06,530
I was smiling because
you're dressed a bit funny.

10
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,320
What's wrong?

11
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,560
In a bad mood?

12
00:02:16,030 --> 00:02:17,030
You look ready to blow at any second.

13
00:02:17,030 --> 00:02:17,890
What happened?

14
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:21,079
I just went to
a hometown association gathering.

15
00:02:21,079 --> 00:02:22,240
Someone there said

16
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:26,240
we from the East Chemical Plant
don't count as Tiecheng locals.

17
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,440
Just because of that?

18
00:02:28,180 --> 00:02:30,430
If you ask me,
you shouldn't have gone at all.

19
00:02:30,430 --> 00:02:31,490
A guy from our plant

20
00:02:31,650 --> 00:02:33,180
who was a few grades above me

21
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,360
once told me that back in their day,

22
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,520
when they went to
hometown association gatherings,

23
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:39,320
people didn't even treat him
like one of their own.

24
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:40,120
In their eyes,

25
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,700
our Third Front Plant area

26
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:43,329
is its own separate world.

27
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,240
They invited me to one
a couple of days ago.

28
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,079
But I thought,

29
00:02:46,180 --> 00:02:47,840
why would I go? To get bullied?

30
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,560
But we did grow up there.

31
00:02:51,810 --> 00:02:53,810
If not there, then where are we from?

32
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:56,380
We are children of the Third Front.

33
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:57,520
They look down on us?

34
00:02:57,520 --> 00:03:00,080
Guess what—
we don't think much of them either.

35
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:00,810
If you ask me,

36
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,430
we should start our own Third Front Plant
hometown association gatherings,

37
00:03:03,430 --> 00:03:04,680
and you should be the president.

38
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:07,610
That's what I call
true brotherhood across the land.

39
00:03:21,270 --> 00:03:23,400
Xiaodan, come out with me for a moment.

40
00:03:39,310 --> 00:03:40,040
Senior Chen.

41
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:43,430
I know what you want to say.

42
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,750
But I want to tell you

43
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:49,960
that I already have a boyfriend.
His name is Zhang Xiaoman.

44
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:50,990
He's my childhood friend,

45
00:03:50,990 --> 00:03:52,079
and we're really close.

46
00:03:52,079 --> 00:03:53,470
Even though we're long-distance now,

47
00:03:53,470 --> 00:03:55,070
our relationship is stable.

48
00:03:55,079 --> 00:03:55,710
We aren't breaking up,

49
00:03:55,710 --> 00:03:56,870
nor do we plan to.

50
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,800
I'll still be with him in the future,

51
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,870
and he's the only one I want to be with.

52
00:04:00,870 --> 00:04:02,530
I won't consider anyone else.

53
00:04:02,710 --> 00:04:05,970
And of course, there's no one else there
for me to consider.

54
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:13,280
If I said or did anything before

55
00:04:13,310 --> 00:04:15,110
that made you get the wrong idea,

56
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:17,390
I'm sorry.

57
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:22,310
Xiaodan.

58
00:04:23,070 --> 00:04:24,510
Your parents and mine

59
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:26,730
did think about setting us up,

60
00:04:28,630 --> 00:04:30,870
and I admit that I have feelings for you.

61
00:04:32,630 --> 00:04:34,230
But please don't be nervous.

62
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:37,600
Xiaodan, you're
a wonderful younger sister.

63
00:04:38,130 --> 00:04:39,040
And my feelings for you

64
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:40,720
are just that—feelings.

65
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:44,650
That's good. That's good.

66
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:48,480
With all this back and forth,

67
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,130
it almost sounds like you rejected me.

68
00:04:51,870 --> 00:04:54,470
I feel relieved
now that we've cleared the air.

69
00:04:55,870 --> 00:04:56,470
Xiaodan.

70
00:04:56,870 --> 00:04:59,430
We haven't even started yet,

71
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,070
so there's no "rejection" here.

72
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:01,870
Right, right.

73
00:05:01,870 --> 00:05:03,630
So go back to your reading.

74
00:05:03,870 --> 00:05:04,800
I'm off to class.

75
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:06,240
Bye-bye.

76
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:06,870
Bye-bye.

77
00:05:19,630 --> 00:05:20,560
Too small again?

78
00:05:21,310 --> 00:05:22,190
Off by 0.66cm.

79
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:24,850
Close enough. 0.66cm is fine.

80
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,630
We haven't been practicing that long.

81
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:28,480
Especially that this thing

82
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,510
keeps buzzing like crazy—

83
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:31,460
feels just like being in an English class.

84
00:05:31,460 --> 00:05:32,920
It's giving me a headache.

85
00:05:33,810 --> 00:05:35,120
-It's not fine.
-Let's have a rest and drink some water.

86
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,720
This is your livelihood.

87
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,380
You have to learn it properly.

88
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,250
Stop talking nonsense all day.

89
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:46,010
You know the labor benefits
in our plant?

90
00:05:46,510 --> 00:05:48,560
In summer, it's tea;

91
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,480
and in winter, it's sugar water.

92
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,940
But for us, it's just plain boiled water.

93
00:05:53,159 --> 00:05:55,000
So astringent and tasteless.

94
00:05:55,510 --> 00:05:56,310
You know what?

95
00:05:57,159 --> 00:05:59,360
Be grateful you have anything to drink.

96
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,360
I had to boil this water myself.

97
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:03,820
Otherwise, you wouldn't even have this.

98
00:06:04,810 --> 00:06:06,070
I've thought about it.

99
00:06:07,270 --> 00:06:08,160
When I officially join our plant,

100
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,960
I won't necessarily do this job.

101
00:06:10,650 --> 00:06:13,510
If I can't handle this, I'll go to
the Maintenance Workshop instead.

102
00:06:13,510 --> 00:06:14,120
This stuff...

103
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,950
Maintenance is much simpler than this.

104
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:18,360
I have a talent for that, you know?

105
00:06:19,070 --> 00:06:20,930
Take our alarm clock for example.

106
00:06:21,310 --> 00:06:23,710
I can take it apart
and put it back together.

107
00:06:24,310 --> 00:06:25,640
E-Even with this thing,

108
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:26,750
I can take it apart

109
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:28,190
and reassemble it with my eyes closed.

110
00:06:28,190 --> 00:06:28,920
Give me a break.

111
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,680
You'll only end up with spare parts
all over the floor.

112
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:31,600
I mean it. Rest assured.

113
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:32,360
Don't mess around.

114
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,070
Let me show you.

115
00:06:33,070 --> 00:06:34,200
Just have your rest.

116
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,510
Don't mess with my machine.

117
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:36,159
It's fine.

118
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:39,480
You know what?

119
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:42,000
I heard an expert is coming today

120
00:06:42,159 --> 00:06:43,560
to give us some pointers.

121
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,800
You'd better listen carefully.

122
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,830
What expert?

123
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:47,190
You're asking for a kicking
messing around here,

124
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:47,870
I'm telling you.

125
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:48,360
You...

126
00:06:51,630 --> 00:06:52,290
Mr. Zhuang.

127
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,860
So you're the expert he talked about?

128
00:07:06,580 --> 00:07:08,110
What the hell did you lathe?

129
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:09,720
Do you have no hands,

130
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,440
no eyes,

131
00:07:10,610 --> 00:07:11,530
or no brain?

132
00:07:13,530 --> 00:07:16,730
Mr. Zhuang, I-I've only been learning this
for a few days.

133
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,120
Is this what you learned?

134
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:21,240
The work uniform
has three tightness requirements.

135
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:21,640
Right.

136
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:23,250
Tight collar, tight cuffs,

137
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,160
and tight hem.

138
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:26,600
If you get dragged into the machine,

139
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,460
it'll be too late for regrets.

140
00:07:35,190 --> 00:07:35,850
Mr. Zhuang.

141
00:07:36,070 --> 00:07:36,600
Xiaoman.

142
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,780
It's off by 0.66cm.

143
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,020
Mr. Zhuang.

144
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,510
You could tell it's off by 0.66cm

145
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:48,680
without even using a caliper?

146
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,920
My eyes are my ruler.

147
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:52,190
Thousands upon thousands of these

148
00:07:52,190 --> 00:07:53,850
have passed through my hands.

149
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,159
As expected from you, Mr. Zhuang.

150
00:07:56,159 --> 00:07:59,360
Being a Grade 8 turner is no joke.

151
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:00,710
You've got real skills.

152
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:04,680
It's a shame.
Though I've got all my skills,

153
00:08:05,950 --> 00:08:07,280
that little brat of mine

154
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:10,000
took off running the very first day

155
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:11,530
he put on his work uniform,

156
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,920
like he was being tortured.

157
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,720
Why didn't you guys stop him?

158
00:08:15,510 --> 00:08:16,170
Mr. Zhuang.

159
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:17,800
Zhuang Sen

160
00:08:17,870 --> 00:08:20,800
has his own dreams and pursuits, right?

161
00:08:21,190 --> 00:08:22,830
It's okay. We are still here.

162
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:24,170
We'll carry on

163
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:25,360
this legacy for you.

164
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:25,800
Don't worry.

165
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,000
Carry on what legacy?

166
00:08:27,310 --> 00:08:28,240
I'm not dead yet.

167
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,510
Alright, alright.

168
00:08:29,510 --> 00:08:30,720
If you want to learn,

169
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:31,680
I'll teach you.

170
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:34,169
You've got to carry it forward

171
00:08:34,549 --> 00:08:35,280
and show them

172
00:08:35,669 --> 00:08:38,010
that East Chemical
has a new generation ready to take over.

173
00:08:38,010 --> 00:08:39,559
For sure, Mr. Zhuang. Don't worry.

174
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:40,559
We'll learn well.

175
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:44,440
Mr. Ding,

176
00:08:44,470 --> 00:08:46,720
aren't you going to count
the bonus I just gave you?

177
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:47,270
Count it?

178
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:49,000
Would you dare shortchange me?

179
00:08:49,510 --> 00:08:51,110
You've got some nerve, Zhao.

180
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:52,490
By the way, Mr. Ding.

181
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:53,210
Our plant

182
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:54,170
has announced

183
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,200
a new financial regulation.

184
00:08:56,510 --> 00:08:59,240
Basically, for healthy adults

185
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,320
without illnesses or injuries,

186
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:02,790
from now on, no subsidies will be given.

187
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,030
Xiaoman

188
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:06,210
turned 18 6 months ago,

189
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:07,960
so he's considered an adult now.

190
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,360
Tell him that from now on,

191
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:12,080
he won't be receiving
that 100 yuan anymore.

192
00:09:13,670 --> 00:09:15,070
He won't be receiving it?

193
00:09:17,510 --> 00:09:18,020
What's that supposed to mean?

194
00:09:18,020 --> 00:09:20,320
Our plant won't take care of
its own children anymore?

195
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,750
It's not that
we're not taking care of them.

196
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:22,960
Meals in our cafeteria

197
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:23,920
are still free;

198
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:26,200
and if they have any
minor illness or injury,

199
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:28,200
our plant hospital still covers it.

200
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:30,510
It's just the 100 yuan pocket money
that's stopping.

201
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:31,600
What kind of nonsense is that?

202
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:33,730
Xiaoman hasn't received a salary yet.

203
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:34,790
There are tens of thousands of people
in our plant.

204
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:36,390
Are you short of his 100 yuan?

205
00:09:37,390 --> 00:09:39,960
Mr. Ding, you can't put it that way.

206
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:42,360
There has to be an end to subsidies.

207
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:44,720
If Xiaoman never works,

208
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:46,000
is our plant supposed to

209
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,930
provide his pocket money for life?

210
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:49,570
Tell you what, Zhao.

211
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:54,000
As for Xiaoman's monthly 100 yuan subsidy,

212
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:56,040
I'll cover it.

213
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,130
You'll cover it?

214
00:09:58,030 --> 00:09:59,600
Then how am I supposed to
do the accounting for this sum?

215
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,600
What do you mean?

216
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:02,350
Forget the accounts.

217
00:10:03,630 --> 00:10:05,000
Just keep it to yourself.

218
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,510
Don't tell anyone about it.

219
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:07,390
If Xiaoman ever asks you,

220
00:10:07,390 --> 00:10:09,630
just tell him
you've given the money to me.

221
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:10,890
The kid is too pitiful.

222
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,090
Okay.

223
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,960
I know what to do, Mr. Ding.

224
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:15,790
If you ask me,

225
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:19,000
you're not treating Xiaoman like a godson,

226
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,570
more like your own son.

227
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,360
You scared me.

228
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,620
You didn't even knock.

229
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:47,910
Well, you didn't lock the door.

230
00:10:47,910 --> 00:10:48,410
You scared me.

231
00:10:48,410 --> 00:10:49,410
The door was open.

232
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:57,750
What did Xiaodan send you?
It smells so good.

233
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:58,750
Let me have a look.

234
00:10:59,150 --> 00:10:59,790
You smelled it?

235
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:00,450
Yeah, I did.

236
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,810
You've got a sharp nose.

237
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,260
Take a look.

238
00:11:10,260 --> 00:11:11,660
Why does it smell so good?

239
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,320
I want to get one for Lulu too.

240
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,450
Where did you get it?

241
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,240
It's the scent of osmanthus.

242
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,440
Bet you didn't know that.

243
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:22,000
We don't seem to have that stuff
around here.

244
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:25,360
In Shanghai, the streets are lined with
osmanthus trees.

245
00:11:25,550 --> 00:11:26,790
When the season comes and they bloom,

246
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:29,450
the whole street smells like this.
It's lovely.

247
00:11:29,790 --> 00:11:31,450
They are all over the streets?

248
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:35,160
So Xiaodan just picked some up
and sent them to you?

249
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:37,360
Can't you talk properly?

250
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:38,470
If not, just go home.

251
00:11:38,470 --> 00:11:40,070
Just kidding. Just kidding.

252
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:43,350
What are you here for?

253
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:48,020
You spent the whole afternoon

254
00:11:48,020 --> 00:11:49,020
just...

255
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:50,510
Just welding this thing?

256
00:11:50,510 --> 00:11:51,360
No. There's also this.

257
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,420
There's also this.

258
00:11:57,510 --> 00:11:59,150
This... A kitchen knife?

259
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,020
It's a bit crooked.

260
00:12:01,150 --> 00:12:02,440
But if this is meant to be
a slicing knife,

261
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:03,370
it's a bit short.

262
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,450
It's a toothbrush made for you.

263
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,060
What's wrong with your eyes? This...

264
00:12:13,420 --> 00:12:14,820
This is a sailboat, okay?

265
00:12:16,790 --> 00:12:17,450
A sailboat.

266
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,490
Oh, it's a sailboat?

267
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,670
It looks a bit like one. It does.

268
00:12:24,670 --> 00:12:25,750
So it's a sailboat.

269
00:12:25,910 --> 00:12:27,150
What do you mean "a bit like one"?

270
00:12:27,150 --> 00:12:28,480
It is a sailboat.

271
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:29,960
But look.

272
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:32,240
Isn't it just a locomotive,

273
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:34,360
with a front part added,

274
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:35,820
and then this thing on top?

275
00:12:36,670 --> 00:12:38,790
Now that you said it,
this half does look like a locomotive.

276
00:12:38,790 --> 00:12:39,790
But you should indeed

277
00:12:39,790 --> 00:12:42,600
send this thing to Xiaodan

278
00:12:43,550 --> 00:12:44,480
and let Xiaodan

279
00:12:44,510 --> 00:12:46,000
analyze it for you

280
00:12:46,550 --> 00:12:47,810
with her artistic eye.

281
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:50,050
Can't you just buy one?

282
00:12:51,550 --> 00:12:52,240
Why?

283
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,900
It's the thought that counts.

284
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,320
If you just buy one on the street,

285
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:57,030
what's the point?

286
00:12:57,030 --> 00:12:58,320
I made this myself.

287
00:12:58,320 --> 00:12:59,360
Good or bad,

288
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:03,000
I put my heart, time, and energy

289
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,150
into this.

290
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:06,480
I-Isn't that much better than buying one?

291
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:08,290
Besides, if I buy it...

292
00:13:10,150 --> 00:13:13,280
I have to save my money
for travel expenses to Shanghai, you know.

293
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,960
But if you give her this,

294
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,240
Xiaodan will think

295
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:19,170
we're learning from a PE coach.

296
00:13:20,150 --> 00:13:21,350
Cut the crap. Come on.

297
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:23,090
Polish the sail. Make it shine.

298
00:13:23,270 --> 00:13:24,750
Why polish it?

299
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,790
Just go find Mr. Zhuang.

300
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,300
You've got an expert right there.

301
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,320
What for?

302
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:35,000
To make this thing.
It'd be great if he taught you.

303
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:38,990
I can't impose on him.

304
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:40,600
It's okay.

305
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,790
Just buy him two bottles of wine.

306
00:13:42,790 --> 00:13:43,910
Doesn't that cost money as well?

307
00:13:43,910 --> 00:13:45,600
How much can wine cost?

308
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,740
Hurry up. Go to your house

309
00:13:46,740 --> 00:13:49,000
and bring two bottles.

310
00:13:49,030 --> 00:13:49,960
From my brother?

311
00:13:50,510 --> 00:13:50,960
Don't bring that many.

312
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:52,360
J-Just bring one bottle.

313
00:13:52,770 --> 00:13:54,080
Wait for me at the unit door.

314
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:54,910
Hurry, hurry.

315
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:55,610
Be quick.

316
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:56,750
Don't bring anything too expensive,

317
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:57,750
or your brother will beat you up.

318
00:13:57,750 --> 00:13:58,480
Don't worry.

319
00:14:30,910 --> 00:14:31,510
Excuse me.

320
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,080
You can't just throw away scrap like that.

321
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,010
There's a trash can right up ahead.

322
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:37,080
Ma'am, this isn't trash.

323
00:14:37,670 --> 00:14:39,390
My boyfriend gave this to me.

324
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:45,310
It's a boat.

325
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,480
It's a boat. Look.

326
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:48,090
Oh, a boat...

327
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:49,080
It's a boat.

328
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:52,200
It looks quite expensive.

329
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,030
I really don't understand
young people these days.

330
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:57,160
It was thoughtful of him to make a boat.

331
00:15:01,510 --> 00:15:02,750
I'm going to an exhibition later,

332
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:04,350
so I won't be home for dinner.

333
00:15:06,070 --> 00:15:07,490
Why are you going out again?

334
00:15:07,490 --> 00:15:09,120
You won't be home for dinner
again, Sweetie?

335
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:11,120
If I want to have a meal with you
in the future,

336
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:13,720
do I have to submit a report first
or something?

337
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:25,670
Of course you don't need a report
to eat with me.

338
00:15:25,670 --> 00:15:27,750
I'm the one who has to report to you.

339
00:15:28,670 --> 00:15:31,080
Well, I have a request.

340
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:34,370
I want to go back to
East Chemical Plant for winter break.

341
00:15:34,510 --> 00:15:35,120
Denied.

342
00:15:36,870 --> 00:15:37,480
Why?

343
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:40,620
It's your first year back in Shanghai,
you know?

344
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:42,680
Your mom has so many relatives here.

345
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:44,680
You... You have to visit them then.

346
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:47,720
They're all looking forward to seeing you.

347
00:15:48,010 --> 00:15:50,270
I haven't seen anyone from our plant
for 6 months.

348
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:52,580
Yan, talk nicely.

349
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:56,600
Sweetie, you just got to Shanghai.

350
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:59,550
You need to make some friends here.

351
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:00,910
You also need to fit in here in Shanghai,

352
00:16:00,910 --> 00:16:01,320
right?

353
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:02,640
Besides,

354
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,870
try to be understanding of your father.

355
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:07,080
He's been away for so many years.

356
00:16:07,390 --> 00:16:09,550
He needs to reconnect

357
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:11,240
with his old friends here.

358
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,370
What does that have to do with me?

359
00:16:13,370 --> 00:16:14,770
He can just go by himself.

360
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:21,840
How can he go by himself?

361
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:24,750
Those relatives and friends of ours
are all coming to see you.

362
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,080
For your sake, you know?

363
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:27,870
Besides, families are supposed to

364
00:16:27,870 --> 00:16:29,960
spend the holidays together.

365
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,910
We can't spend them apart, right?

366
00:16:31,910 --> 00:16:33,240
You are usually so busy.

367
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,220
You've got to spend some more time

368
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:36,240
with your father and me
during the holidays,

369
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:36,750
right?

370
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:44,480
Then I want to go back to
East Chemical Plant for summer break.

371
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:45,120
Okay.

372
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:46,630
I can't be bothered with you.

373
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:48,360
Okay, go back for summer break.

374
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,270
I promise you.

375
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,630
You can go back for summer break.

376
00:16:51,630 --> 00:16:52,300
Does this look pretty?

377
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:53,360
Yeah, it's pretty.

378
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:59,220
The food in Shanghai must be good.

379
00:16:59,220 --> 00:17:00,680
You've put on some weight.

380
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,550
How was it? Did you miss us?

381
00:17:03,550 --> 00:17:04,550
I haven't gained any weight.

382
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:05,109
Of course—

383
00:17:05,109 --> 00:17:06,310
of course I missed you guys.

384
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:08,710
Seeing you guys
makes me feel like I'm home.

385
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,130
Not bad, Xia Lei.

386
00:17:11,310 --> 00:17:12,750
Your accent hasn't changed.

387
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:14,680
I thought coming back from Shanghai,

388
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,960
you'd be speaking all la-di-da.

389
00:17:17,030 --> 00:17:17,960
It's "Ala, ala."

390
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:18,400
What la-di-da?

391
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:19,960
What the hell is "la-di-da"?

392
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,460
Xiaodan is the one who speaks like that.

393
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:23,190
She's got that Shanghai blood.

394
00:17:26,020 --> 00:17:28,050
Why do you have to bring up
something so sensitive?

395
00:17:28,050 --> 00:17:29,510
You started it,

396
00:17:29,510 --> 00:17:30,510
with your "la-di-da."

397
00:17:30,510 --> 00:17:31,680
Well, anyway,

398
00:17:31,830 --> 00:17:33,310
although Xiaodan isn't coming back
this year,

399
00:17:33,310 --> 00:17:35,370
she'll definitely be back next year.

400
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:37,480
As long as East Chemical Plant stands,

401
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:38,660
we won't scatter, right?

402
00:17:38,660 --> 00:17:40,460
-Right, we won't scatter.
-Yes.

403
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:42,480
I've talked to Xiaodan on the phone.

404
00:17:42,550 --> 00:17:45,810
She's spending New Year's
with her family there this year.

405
00:17:46,310 --> 00:17:48,110
Well, it's fine if she doesn't come back,

406
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:49,110
but you have to come back.

407
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:50,030
I won't accept it if you don't come back.

408
00:17:50,030 --> 00:17:52,240
E-Even if I do come back,
it won't be because of you.

409
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,440
I'm coming back for my parents.

410
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,550
Whatever the reason.

411
00:17:54,550 --> 00:17:56,240
You just have to come back.
You have to be here,

412
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:56,860
you know?

413
00:17:57,030 --> 00:17:58,090
Alright, alright.

414
00:18:00,550 --> 00:18:01,920
I-I heard from my dad

415
00:18:02,310 --> 00:18:04,550
that our plant isn't doing so well.

416
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:06,030
It's doing okay.

417
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:08,310
Look at my 100 yuan a month—

418
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:09,370
it's always been paid right on time.

419
00:18:09,370 --> 00:18:10,300
No delays at all.

420
00:18:11,270 --> 00:18:12,670
That's pretty good then.

421
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:13,880
In my dorm,

422
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:15,880
there's another Third Front child.

423
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:17,400
He said back in his hometown,

424
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,440
their plant is doing poorly.

425
00:18:20,030 --> 00:18:20,750
That's just them.

426
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:22,310
You know, our plant is different.

427
00:18:22,310 --> 00:18:23,750
Our plant won't be like that.

428
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:27,030
Dongdong and I learn skills
at the technical school every day.

429
00:18:27,030 --> 00:18:29,030
We're going full steam,
ready to take up our posts anytime.

430
00:18:29,030 --> 00:18:30,110
We're just waiting for it.

431
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:31,640
Good. That's good.

432
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:38,070
We're at Huiliu River.

433
00:18:38,070 --> 00:18:39,310
Are we entering the plant area?

434
00:18:39,310 --> 00:18:40,680
Yeah, we're almost home.

435
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:43,680
What's the first thing you want to do
when you get home?

436
00:18:44,980 --> 00:18:46,110
I want to take a bath.

437
00:18:47,110 --> 00:18:48,310
Let's do it. No problem.

438
00:18:48,310 --> 00:18:49,150
We'll go take a bath right away.

439
00:18:49,150 --> 00:18:49,630
Okay.

440
00:19:00,270 --> 00:19:02,640
Put some strength into it.
I haven't had a good scrub in ages.

441
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:04,440
Just trust my scrubbing skills.

442
00:19:05,470 --> 00:19:07,270
I'm almost a semi-pro scrubber.

443
00:19:09,010 --> 00:19:10,270
Look at all this grime.

444
00:19:10,310 --> 00:19:13,240
You haven't had a scrub
in at least 6 months, have you?

445
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:15,030
Good for you.

446
00:19:17,040 --> 00:19:18,840
You've been soaking for a while.

447
00:19:20,350 --> 00:19:21,550
Don't you feel dizzy?

448
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,200
It feels good.

449
00:19:24,510 --> 00:19:25,270
So good.

450
00:19:27,110 --> 00:19:28,260
You don't understand.

451
00:19:28,260 --> 00:19:29,990
When winter comes in Shanghai,

452
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,920
the cold wind chills you to the bone.

453
00:19:33,510 --> 00:19:34,000
I just thought,

454
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,030
if there were a hot bath pool,

455
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:37,960
I'd dive right in.

456
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:42,440
Wait, doesn't Shanghai have bathhouses?

457
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:44,710
Well, the school doesn't.

458
00:19:45,030 --> 00:19:45,830
Just showers.

459
00:19:47,310 --> 00:19:49,510
The nights in Shanghai are unbearable.

460
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:52,190
I'd sleep hugging a hot water bottle,

461
00:19:52,190 --> 00:19:54,450
but by the next morning, it'd be ice cold.

462
00:19:55,780 --> 00:19:56,670
Sometimes

463
00:19:57,050 --> 00:19:58,970
my legs would cramp and wake me up.

464
00:19:59,510 --> 00:20:01,030
Isn't that kind of ridiculous?

465
00:20:01,030 --> 00:20:03,350
Is it that bad? It's the south, after all.

466
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:04,510
It can't be even colder than here.

467
00:20:04,510 --> 00:20:06,110
It's different in the south.

468
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:08,180
Their cold is damp and penetrating.

469
00:20:08,180 --> 00:20:10,070
Plus, there's no central heating
in the south.

470
00:20:10,070 --> 00:20:12,070
It's not warm like it is here at home.

471
00:20:14,310 --> 00:20:15,970
That does sound like torture.

472
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:18,550
Apart from the cold,

473
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:19,610
what else is there?

474
00:20:20,140 --> 00:20:20,880
In Shanghai?

475
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:29,340
Well, Shanghai

476
00:20:30,590 --> 00:20:32,920
is a very big city.

477
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:34,830
It's huge—

478
00:20:35,550 --> 00:20:37,030
too big for me to handle.

479
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:39,770
It gives me a sort of...

480
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:42,080
A sort of loneliness.

481
00:20:42,790 --> 00:20:43,310
What?

482
00:20:44,350 --> 00:20:45,080
Loneliness.

483
00:20:45,790 --> 00:20:46,720
You feel lonely?

484
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:50,480
Why would you feel lonely?
There are so many people in Shanghai.

485
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:51,680
How can you be lonely?

486
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:55,550
It's not about how many people there are.

487
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:56,550
It's just that...

488
00:20:57,030 --> 00:20:58,550
They are all strangers.

489
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,440
The way they look at you, it's just...

490
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:02,350
It's like you're a... A bumpkin.

491
00:21:05,790 --> 00:21:07,840
What about school? Your classmates?

492
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:08,880
Don't they hang out with you?

493
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:11,480
Classmates... My classmates are fine.

494
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,640
Everyone's busy with their own stuff.

495
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:15,070
It's not like in our plant.

496
00:21:15,070 --> 00:21:16,200
We're so close here.

497
00:21:16,550 --> 00:21:17,480
It's different.

498
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:22,650
I went to
a hometown association gathering once,

499
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:24,960
but I felt I couldn't fit in.

500
00:21:25,310 --> 00:21:27,770
It felt like
I'm not really a Tiecheng local.

501
00:21:29,110 --> 00:21:29,720
They...

502
00:21:31,310 --> 00:21:32,680
You know, when I'm out there,

503
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:34,790
I don't even know where I'm really from.

504
00:21:34,790 --> 00:21:37,640
Well, if you mean strictly Tiecheng,

505
00:21:37,790 --> 00:21:38,720
we don't count as locals.

506
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:40,720
But our East Chemical Plant
is quite an important area.

507
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:42,580
They still won't hang out with us.

508
00:21:44,590 --> 00:21:45,350
Fireworks!

509
00:21:45,350 --> 00:21:46,880
Time to set off fireworks!

510
00:21:48,070 --> 00:21:48,930
Happy New Year!

511
00:21:50,310 --> 00:21:52,040
Happy New Year. Happy New Year.

512
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:56,650
♪ Smoke from the chimney drifted
back in those days ♪

513
00:21:56,720 --> 00:21:57,830
Happy New Year.

514
00:21:57,050 --> 00:22:00,900
♪ Distant friends waving their hands ♪

515
00:21:59,550 --> 00:22:01,000
Happy New Year.

516
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:05,130
♪ From some yard wall comes a whistle ♪

517
00:22:03,510 --> 00:22:04,790
Run the cord. Is it long enough?

518
00:22:04,790 --> 00:22:07,030
It's long enough. It's 20 meters long.

519
00:22:05,320 --> 00:22:09,410
♪ Blowing the years running along ♪

520
00:22:07,110 --> 00:22:08,070
There's plenty of slack.

521
00:22:08,070 --> 00:22:08,790
I bought 20 meters.

522
00:22:08,790 --> 00:22:09,960
That's enough. It reached.

523
00:22:09,950 --> 00:22:13,910
♪ You're always on my mind ♪

524
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:10,590
Right?

525
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:12,610
I got tangled up.

526
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:17,860
♪ How are you doing now? ♪

527
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:15,130
How is it? Does it work?

528
00:22:15,130 --> 00:22:15,720
This works.

529
00:22:15,720 --> 00:22:17,520
This cord you bought is perfect.

530
00:22:18,350 --> 00:22:22,400
♪ Would you know me when we meet again? ♪

531
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:26,750
♪ I grew tall through all the goodbyes ♪

532
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:24,720
Hello? Hello?

533
00:22:24,830 --> 00:22:25,360
Xiaodan?

534
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:26,490
Xiaodan!

535
00:22:27,310 --> 00:22:28,170
Say something.

536
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:29,270
Xiaodan, it's Xia Lei!

537
00:22:28,820 --> 00:22:32,560
♪ The one who wept with longing ♪

538
00:22:29,550 --> 00:22:30,640
Xiaoman, Xia Lei.

539
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,350
We're sitting on the balcony.

540
00:22:32,350 --> 00:22:33,550
He bought a really long phone cord,

541
00:22:32,730 --> 00:22:36,410
♪ Home is where your heart
stays attached ♪

542
00:22:33,550 --> 00:22:35,680
so we can bring the phone to the window
to watch the fireworks together with you.

543
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:37,040
Yeah, we're watching at my place.

544
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:41,320
♪ Those cheeks flushed red in heavy snow ♪

545
00:22:37,350 --> 00:22:38,880
Wait a sec. I'll find a spot too.

546
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:39,680
Let me see.

547
00:22:40,550 --> 00:22:41,590
I found one. I found one.

548
00:22:41,340 --> 00:22:45,320
♪ The smoke that rose to welcome me home ♪

549
00:22:44,110 --> 00:22:44,720
They've started, Xiaodan.

550
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:45,880
They've set off fireworks here.

551
00:22:45,880 --> 00:22:49,830
♪ The one I saw just by turning around ♪

552
00:22:49,940 --> 00:22:53,480
♪ Home is where the door's left open
for me ♪

553
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:51,900
They've started here as well!

554
00:22:54,070 --> 00:22:55,160
There was a red one here, Xiaodan.

555
00:22:54,290 --> 00:22:58,580
♪ Trains keep rushing forward nonstop ♪

556
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:57,550
The one here just now was red too.

557
00:22:58,620 --> 00:23:02,580
♪ But I go against the signs to find her ♪

558
00:23:00,070 --> 00:23:01,270
Another red one!

559
00:23:01,550 --> 00:23:02,550
Yours was red too?

560
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:05,520
Then we're watching
the same fireworks, Xiaodan.

561
00:23:05,570 --> 00:23:09,670
♪ The neighbors' palm fans,
the crickets' chirping ♪

562
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:08,000
Is it almost time for the countdown?

563
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:08,730
Let me check.

564
00:23:10,030 --> 00:23:13,630
♪ Mouths full of tiny floral patterns,
eyes smiling ♪

565
00:23:10,110 --> 00:23:11,590
Xiaodan, it's almost time.

566
00:23:11,590 --> 00:23:12,510
Keep an eye on the clock.

567
00:23:12,510 --> 00:23:14,030
Let's count down together.

568
00:23:14,030 --> 00:23:15,440
Wait, wait. Let me see.

569
00:23:14,180 --> 00:23:17,790
♪ Beside the clivia, the wine cup sways ♪

570
00:23:16,070 --> 00:23:17,800
It's almost time, almost time.

571
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:22,920
-Six, five, four, three, two, one!
-Five, four, three, two, one!

572
00:23:18,290 --> 00:23:22,310
♪ Children listening to stories
can't fall asleep ♪

573
00:23:23,010 --> 00:23:31,630
♪ The moon shines bright, tears glisten ♪

574
00:23:23,270 --> 00:23:24,590
-Happy New Year!
-Happy New Year!

575
00:23:24,590 --> 00:23:25,720
Xiaoman, Xia Lei.

576
00:23:26,110 --> 00:23:28,240
Happy New Year, Xia Lei! Happy New Year!

577
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,970
Happy New Year. Happy New Year.

578
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:39,670
[New Semester, New Hope]

579
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:43,500
What are you...

580
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:44,850
It's fine if you want to pass.

581
00:23:44,850 --> 00:23:46,110
Why do you have to...

582
00:23:47,830 --> 00:23:48,510
A two.

583
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:49,070
Pass.

584
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:50,970
Black Joker.

585
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:51,720
Black Joker played.

586
00:23:51,720 --> 00:23:54,210
Black Joker played?
Then I'll play the Red Joker.

587
00:23:54,210 --> 00:23:54,880
-You go ahead.
-No card to play, huh?

588
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:56,280
You go ahead. Pass for me.

589
00:23:56,510 --> 00:23:57,350
A six.

590
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,160
A nine.

591
00:23:59,380 --> 00:24:00,050
A Jack.

592
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:02,070
What kind of hand is this?

593
00:24:02,070 --> 00:24:03,310
-Hey! What are you doing?
-B-Bomb it.

594
00:24:03,310 --> 00:24:04,350
How can I bomb that?

595
00:24:04,350 --> 00:24:05,590
Bomb. Bomb that.

596
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:06,480
Right, bomb that.

597
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:07,350
Right, you can bomb it.

598
00:24:07,350 --> 00:24:08,680
-Wait, you...
-Four fours.

599
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,270
Four fours? I'll bomb too. Four fives.

600
00:24:10,270 --> 00:24:11,680
What are you doing here?

601
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:13,440
I'm here to see my fellow townsman.

602
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:14,000
Others might not consider you
their fellow townsman,

603
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:14,510
but I do.

604
00:24:14,510 --> 00:24:15,510
Fellow townsman?

605
00:24:15,510 --> 00:24:16,860
Aren't you from "Hujian"?

606
00:24:16,860 --> 00:24:19,520
I heard you speaking fluent Fujianese
with Liu.

607
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:22,720
Buddy, you are way off.

608
00:24:23,030 --> 00:24:24,110
It should be "Hugian."

609
00:24:24,110 --> 00:24:25,420
-Hugian?
-Hugian.

610
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:26,350
-Hugian.
-That's right.

611
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:27,590
Stop it, stop it.

612
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:29,250
What do you want from me?

613
00:24:29,350 --> 00:24:30,350
You're interrupting our game.

614
00:24:30,350 --> 00:24:31,680
Didn't people say you're odd?

615
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:32,960
I prepared a stylish outfit

616
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:34,070
especially for you.

617
00:24:34,070 --> 00:24:36,110
We're in Shanghai now.
We've got to keep up with the times.

618
00:24:36,110 --> 00:24:38,090
Locals here all wear leather jackets,

619
00:24:38,090 --> 00:24:39,330
jeans, and sneakers.

620
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:40,540
Look at you.

621
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:43,940
So you've got the jeans and sneakers.

622
00:24:43,940 --> 00:24:46,070
You just need the leather jacket then.

623
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:49,650
What do you think?

624
00:24:49,650 --> 00:24:50,080
You...

625
00:24:50,960 --> 00:24:53,220
But I don't have any spare money for this.

626
00:24:53,730 --> 00:24:55,180
If you're giving it to me for free,
then I'll take it.

627
00:24:55,180 --> 00:24:56,040
What about you?

628
00:24:56,090 --> 00:24:56,830
I'll pass.

629
00:24:57,550 --> 00:24:58,640
It's not my style.

630
00:24:58,750 --> 00:24:59,750
It's exactly your style.

631
00:24:59,750 --> 00:25:00,440
Forget it.

632
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:01,440
And you?

633
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:03,950
I'd rather buy drumsticks
with that money.

634
00:25:03,950 --> 00:25:04,890
I'm not vain.

635
00:25:05,070 --> 00:25:06,310
What do you mean vain?

636
00:25:06,990 --> 00:25:08,920
I-I'll look around some more then.

637
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:10,920
No hard feelings if we don't make a deal.

638
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:12,110
Feel free to ask me for anything.

639
00:25:12,110 --> 00:25:12,960
Or ask Lei.

640
00:25:13,030 --> 00:25:13,920
He's my best friend.

641
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:15,640
-Lei.
-Lei.

642
00:25:16,110 --> 00:25:17,310
-I'm off then.
-Okay.

643
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,720
-Bye-bye.
-Bye-bye.

644
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:19,480
Take care.

645
00:25:20,240 --> 00:25:21,170
Whose turn is it?

646
00:25:22,070 --> 00:25:22,750
Careful!

647
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:29,060
Saving money to go visit Xiaodan?

648
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,660
You're quite devoted.

649
00:25:32,750 --> 00:25:33,380
Of course.

650
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,760
Do you think things will work out

651
00:25:39,510 --> 00:25:40,910
between you and Xiaodan?

652
00:25:41,750 --> 00:25:42,640
Why not?

653
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:44,400
We're... Good.

654
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:50,410
She's in college in Shanghai.

655
00:25:53,310 --> 00:25:54,910
So what if she's in Shanghai?

656
00:25:55,250 --> 00:25:57,050
Even though she's not by my side,

657
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:58,680
our bond won't be broken.

658
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:00,810
Exactly. So what if she's in Shanghai?

659
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:02,110
Back then,

660
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:03,960
many couples at our plant lived apart,

661
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:05,310
but in the end they still
got back together.

662
00:26:05,310 --> 00:26:06,510
Jobs were assigned back then.

663
00:26:06,510 --> 00:26:07,610
No one's giving you any job now, you know?

664
00:26:07,610 --> 00:26:08,880
It's even better that way.

665
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:11,440
If no one's giving you a job,
you can go wherever you want.

666
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:13,350
Yeah, I've been thinking.

667
00:26:13,820 --> 00:26:16,100
After Xiaodan graduates,

668
00:26:17,310 --> 00:26:18,710
if she wants to come back,

669
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:21,310
we'll do something here.

670
00:26:22,110 --> 00:26:24,110
If she doesn't want to come back,

671
00:26:24,620 --> 00:26:26,280
I'll go find a job in Shanghai.

672
00:26:30,750 --> 00:26:32,270
Do we have any dried sausages left?

673
00:26:32,270 --> 00:26:32,590
Yes.

674
00:26:32,590 --> 00:26:33,390
Give him some.

675
00:26:33,550 --> 00:26:34,240
He's meeting his father-in-law.

676
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:35,700
He can't go empty-handed.

677
00:26:36,310 --> 00:26:36,830
No need.

678
00:26:37,550 --> 00:26:38,680
Take some, you silly boy.

679
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:40,540
You're still wet behind the ears.

680
00:26:40,790 --> 00:26:41,680
Am I thinking it wrong?

681
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:42,940
Xiaodan and I are fine.

682
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:44,720
Nothing's wrong.

683
00:26:45,040 --> 00:26:46,490
Your heart is in the right place.

684
00:26:46,490 --> 00:26:48,040
Just go... Just go get the sausages.

685
00:26:48,040 --> 00:26:49,750
Poking your nose into others' business.

686
00:26:49,750 --> 00:26:51,880
He's being silly,
and you're blindly going along with him?

687
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:53,070
Senior Chen, you said

688
00:26:53,070 --> 00:26:55,550
film and architecture use the same method

689
00:26:55,550 --> 00:26:57,350
to construct a space.

690
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:00,400
How do you say that in French again?

691
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:01,200
Montage.

692
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:05,860
-Mon... Mon...
-Montage.

693
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:06,920
Montage.

694
00:27:06,950 --> 00:27:08,360
Are you going to study abroad?

695
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:09,020
No, I'm not.

696
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:11,660
Senior Chen's planning to study abroad.

697
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,550
I'm just attending lectures
and doing research.

698
00:27:13,550 --> 00:27:14,550
That's enough for me.

699
00:27:14,550 --> 00:27:16,280
At most, I'll go on a study tour.

700
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:18,880
Besides, Xiaoman is still at the plant.

701
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:20,830
We only see each other once a year,

702
00:27:20,830 --> 00:27:21,750
twice at most.

703
00:27:22,110 --> 00:27:24,570
I don't want to be apart from him
for too long.

704
00:27:28,110 --> 00:27:29,270
This is the money for...

705
00:27:29,270 --> 00:27:30,200
Accommodation.

706
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:31,960
Food.

707
00:27:33,030 --> 00:27:35,290
What can I do with
just this 100 yuan left?

708
00:27:36,830 --> 00:27:37,850
In the mall,

709
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:40,810
we can't just have a meal.
I need to take her shopping.

710
00:27:42,550 --> 00:27:44,480
Where can I get some more money?

711
00:27:44,680 --> 00:27:45,680
It's all fixed.

712
00:27:46,310 --> 00:27:47,960
Let me know if you need anything else.

713
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:48,550
Xiaoman,

714
00:27:48,720 --> 00:27:49,680
here is 40 yuan for you.

715
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:51,350
Okay. Thank you, Ma'am.

716
00:27:51,350 --> 00:27:52,410
I should thank you.

717
00:27:52,510 --> 00:27:54,350
Call me if any neighbors need help.

718
00:27:54,350 --> 00:27:54,880
If you need anything,

719
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:55,550
I'll come anytime, Ma'am.

720
00:27:55,550 --> 00:27:56,920
-Okay.
-I'll take the trash out.

721
00:27:56,920 --> 00:27:57,200
Okay.

722
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:58,070
Come on, go back inside.

723
00:27:58,070 --> 00:27:59,880
Okay. Thanks, Xiaoman. Take care.

724
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:00,550
Bye, Ma'am.

725
00:28:06,310 --> 00:28:08,590
Go up and re-check it for that old lady.

726
00:28:09,750 --> 00:28:12,310
Mr. Ding, what's this for?

727
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:14,240
Everyone in the plant
knows that Xiaoman is

728
00:28:14,240 --> 00:28:15,820
going to Shanghai to visit Xiaodan,

729
00:28:15,820 --> 00:28:17,680
so we've given all the work to him.

730
00:28:18,590 --> 00:28:20,240
You... You're being a little
too kind to him.

731
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,700
I'm getting a bit jealous.

732
00:28:23,190 --> 00:28:24,190
Just go upstairs.

733
00:28:25,690 --> 00:28:26,210
I...

734
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:28,640
I'm doing the work,
and I have to get kicked?

735
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:35,000
Qing.

736
00:28:36,550 --> 00:28:37,550
Fan, you're here.

737
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:39,030
Do you have a computer to assemble,

738
00:28:39,030 --> 00:28:40,350
or are you bringing me some business?

739
00:28:40,350 --> 00:28:42,240
You set up an experience zone, right?

740
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:43,550
I've brought my buddy here
to "surf" a bit—

741
00:28:43,550 --> 00:28:44,400
to try it out.

742
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:45,720
The computers are right here.

743
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:46,030
Okay.

744
00:28:46,030 --> 00:28:47,110
Go ahead and enjoy yourselves.

745
00:28:47,110 --> 00:28:47,960
Play to your heart's content.

746
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:48,440
Okay.

747
00:28:49,030 --> 00:28:50,110
-You go ahead and do your thing.
-Okay.

748
00:28:50,110 --> 00:28:50,640
Let's go.

749
00:28:51,580 --> 00:28:53,900
[Internet Experience Zone:
5 yuan per hour]

750
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:57,530
Get a feel for it.

751
00:29:02,310 --> 00:29:03,480
Let me be clear upfront—

752
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:04,830
I don't have money to buy a computer.

753
00:29:04,830 --> 00:29:06,030
You should talk to Eight about this.

754
00:29:06,030 --> 00:29:07,180
He'd definitely be interested.

755
00:29:07,180 --> 00:29:09,050
Eight's more suited for an internet cafe.

756
00:29:09,050 --> 00:29:10,580
How can he be the same as you?

757
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:12,590
I can go to an internet cafe too.

758
00:29:12,590 --> 00:29:15,320
Our school also has a network
in the computer lab.

759
00:29:15,720 --> 00:29:17,650
Why do I have to experience it here?

760
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:19,960
Don't you have to pay at an internet cafe?

761
00:29:20,310 --> 00:29:21,440
And what the school computer lab has

762
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:22,680
is a LAN,

763
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:24,020
but this is the internet.

764
00:29:24,020 --> 00:29:25,340
Internet, you know?

765
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,670
What's the difference?
They are both networks.

766
00:29:27,670 --> 00:29:28,720
Just play.

767
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,680
Just try it out. I won't trick you.

768
00:29:31,110 --> 00:29:33,110
Search for something you like.

769
00:29:33,490 --> 00:29:36,550
Right, something you're interested in—
search for it.

770
00:29:39,790 --> 00:29:40,240
Right.

771
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:45,140
This is our East Chemical Plant.

772
00:29:45,140 --> 00:29:46,640
[East Integrated Chemical Plant]

773
00:29:48,110 --> 00:29:48,960
This is Mahavira Hall.

774
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:50,110
We used to play here all the time.

775
00:29:50,110 --> 00:29:50,960
T-This is amazing.

776
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:52,680
This is called information retrieval,

777
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:53,350
understand?

778
00:29:53,350 --> 00:29:55,670
Do you think you can find this
in the school computer lab?

779
00:29:55,670 --> 00:29:56,930
And can it be this fast?

780
00:29:57,550 --> 00:29:59,720
So why did I bring you here today?

781
00:30:00,110 --> 00:30:02,440
I just want you to get a feel
for the future.

782
00:30:02,790 --> 00:30:05,160
Gaming and chatting in internet cafes
is expensive.

783
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:08,020
It's not as convenient as
buying your own computer.

784
00:30:08,290 --> 00:30:10,550
See? I knew you wanted me
to buy a computer.

785
00:30:10,550 --> 00:30:11,750
But I didn't expect

786
00:30:11,750 --> 00:30:12,550
to find our plant here.

787
00:30:12,550 --> 00:30:13,240
East Chemical Plant.

788
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,440
This... This is our family quarters.

789
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:15,350
That's normal.

790
00:30:15,350 --> 00:30:17,080
Let me show you something else.

791
00:30:18,030 --> 00:30:18,770
Look.

792
00:30:21,220 --> 00:30:27,140
[Experience a different kind of
aerial journey]

793
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:22,440
This

794
00:30:22,940 --> 00:30:24,350
is a BBS related to us.

795
00:30:24,960 --> 00:30:27,630
It's the most popular BBS in Shanghai
right now.

796
00:30:27,650 --> 00:30:29,050
You can search for it too.

797
00:30:29,750 --> 00:30:30,160
Right.

798
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:33,520
That's right.

799
00:30:33,880 --> 00:30:34,680
That's right.

800
00:30:35,640 --> 00:30:38,720
Look, it covers food, housing,
and transport in Shanghai,

801
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:40,450
as well as work-related stuff.

802
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:41,360
Right.

803
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:42,680
This is the Arts section.

804
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:44,510
So it's all about art in here, isn't it?

805
00:30:44,510 --> 00:30:46,200
Can't you search for something serious?

806
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:46,960
Stop looking at art.

807
00:30:46,960 --> 00:30:48,510
What does art have to do with you?

808
00:30:48,510 --> 00:30:49,970
Scroll down. Scroll down.

809
00:30:50,350 --> 00:30:51,030
Look at the jobs.

810
00:30:51,030 --> 00:30:52,360
What counts as serious?

811
00:30:52,930 --> 00:30:54,410
This is right. See?

812
00:30:55,110 --> 00:30:56,030
There really is.

813
00:30:56,030 --> 00:30:57,490
-There really is.
-Right?

814
00:30:57,720 --> 00:30:59,550
Do you have MSN?

815
00:31:00,310 --> 00:31:01,000
MSN?

816
00:31:01,310 --> 00:31:01,960
No.

817
00:31:02,350 --> 00:31:05,010
Isn't that just
an instant communication tool?

818
00:31:05,350 --> 00:31:07,550
We've got our cell phones, phone numbers,

819
00:31:07,550 --> 00:31:08,610
and text messages.

820
00:31:09,030 --> 00:31:10,110
So what do we need that for?

821
00:31:10,110 --> 00:31:11,390
You can't even carry it around with you.

822
00:31:11,390 --> 00:31:12,110
Look.

823
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:14,720
I knew you've gotten dumb
from studying at school.

824
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,550
Nowadays, many foreign countries

825
00:31:16,550 --> 00:31:18,070
have gone paperless—

826
00:31:18,930 --> 00:31:21,060
work is all done through the internet.

827
00:31:21,550 --> 00:31:23,350
As long as you have the internet—

828
00:31:23,550 --> 00:31:24,110
think of it this way.

829
00:31:24,110 --> 00:31:26,270
If the computer is a car,

830
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:28,110
then the internet is the highway.

831
00:31:28,110 --> 00:31:29,160
It leads you

832
00:31:30,750 --> 00:31:32,790
towards the future. Got it?

833
00:31:34,240 --> 00:31:35,440
You guys keep eating.

834
00:31:48,090 --> 00:31:50,930
Xiaoman, have some sweet and sour pork.

835
00:31:52,470 --> 00:31:53,790
Right, here.

836
00:31:57,960 --> 00:31:58,820
Have some Coke.

837
00:32:00,690 --> 00:32:01,620
I'm telling you,

838
00:32:01,940 --> 00:32:03,070
don't make that face

839
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:05,140
when you're out and about—

840
00:32:05,690 --> 00:32:07,290
you're asking for a beating.

841
00:32:07,790 --> 00:32:08,200
I...

842
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:10,290
I have a favor to ask you.

843
00:32:10,310 --> 00:32:10,960
What is it?

844
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:12,750
Well,

845
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:16,350
Xiaoman, you've been working on that

846
00:32:16,350 --> 00:32:20,010
pipeline project at our plant,
and you've made quite a lot, right?

847
00:32:20,030 --> 00:32:22,240
You want to borrow money?
I don't have any.

848
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:22,830
Xiaoman.

849
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:24,660
My dear Xiaoman.

850
00:32:24,660 --> 00:32:26,790
I don't have any money. I really don't.

851
00:32:26,830 --> 00:32:28,350
Well, I know

852
00:32:28,970 --> 00:32:32,230
you're saving up to visit Xiaodan
in Shanghai.

853
00:32:32,510 --> 00:32:33,880
But you helped Zhuang Sen.

854
00:32:33,880 --> 00:32:35,400
You can't leave me out.

855
00:32:35,400 --> 00:32:36,480
That's not cool.

856
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:37,300
Besides,

857
00:32:39,460 --> 00:32:41,000
even if you leave everyone else out,
you can't leave me out, right?

858
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,720
What do you mean not cool?

859
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:45,030
Zhuang Sen went to a big city

860
00:32:45,790 --> 00:32:47,510
to p-pursue his dreams, right?

861
00:32:47,510 --> 00:32:49,510
To complete his life experience.

862
00:32:50,030 --> 00:32:52,040
What about you? You're fed
three meals a day at home,

863
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:52,830
and you sleep as soon as you get back.

864
00:32:52,830 --> 00:32:54,290
What do you need money for?

865
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:56,710
Love is my dream.

866
00:32:57,590 --> 00:32:59,400
I was already tight on cash.

867
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:01,120
After I started dating Lulu,

868
00:33:01,190 --> 00:33:03,440
I had to split every penny in half,
you know?

869
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:04,790
Things have gotten even tighter.

870
00:33:04,790 --> 00:33:06,400
Exactly. You don't make much,

871
00:33:06,400 --> 00:33:08,270
yet you're spending money on dating.

872
00:33:08,270 --> 00:33:11,070
Don't you have any idea
how much you actually have?

873
00:33:14,350 --> 00:33:16,810
Dear Xiaoman, can you please
think about it?

874
00:33:18,660 --> 00:33:20,920
You see, here's the thing about
borrowing money—

875
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:23,380
you have to pay back
however much you borrow.

876
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:24,830
Of course I'll pay it back.

877
00:33:24,830 --> 00:33:26,810
I'll pay you as soon as I have money.

878
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:30,110
You have a fixed amount of income
every month,

879
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:32,200
and it's not enough to begin with.

880
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:33,550
If you borrow money from others

881
00:33:33,550 --> 00:33:34,200
and take it home,

882
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:35,440
you're invisibly adding

883
00:33:35,440 --> 00:33:37,310
so much pressure on yourself, right?

884
00:33:37,310 --> 00:33:37,880
Right.

885
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:39,970
Isn't that asking for trouble?

886
00:33:40,390 --> 00:33:41,590
You should think about it this way.

887
00:33:41,590 --> 00:33:44,790
If someone gives you money
that you don't have to pay back,

888
00:33:45,310 --> 00:33:46,240
wouldn't that be great?

889
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:47,570
Of course it'd be great.

890
00:33:48,550 --> 00:33:50,790
I-If I don't borrow from him then,

891
00:33:50,790 --> 00:33:52,440
wouldn't I be a fool?

892
00:33:53,440 --> 00:33:53,970
Alright.

893
00:33:55,270 --> 00:33:56,390
I've thought this through for you.

894
00:33:56,390 --> 00:33:57,680
If you have nothing better to do,

895
00:33:57,680 --> 00:34:00,080
in the mornings, evenings, or on holidays,

896
00:34:01,350 --> 00:34:02,750
don't go running around.

897
00:34:03,270 --> 00:34:05,310
Come out with me to do some work.

898
00:34:06,300 --> 00:34:07,510
I can make up

899
00:34:07,510 --> 00:34:09,030
a-all that little "dating fund"

900
00:34:09,030 --> 00:34:10,159
y-you and Lulu need.

901
00:34:11,110 --> 00:34:11,770
I get it now.

902
00:34:12,190 --> 00:34:15,250
So you want me to work on
this pipeline project with you?

903
00:34:15,949 --> 00:34:16,710
Doesn't that sound good?

904
00:34:16,710 --> 00:34:17,440
Okay, okay.

905
00:34:18,030 --> 00:34:19,880
But let's agree on daily settlement.

906
00:34:19,880 --> 00:34:20,840
If you don't pay me,

907
00:34:20,840 --> 00:34:21,880
I'll go to Mr. Ding

908
00:34:22,030 --> 00:34:23,290
and take your 100 yuan.

909
00:34:23,290 --> 00:34:24,360
Look at you, so unambitious.

910
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:25,190
Would I cheat you out of money?

911
00:34:25,190 --> 00:34:26,389
Would I owe you money?

912
00:34:26,590 --> 00:34:28,030
All these years, only you guys
have owed me money.

913
00:34:28,030 --> 00:34:29,760
When have I ever owed you money?

914
00:34:31,030 --> 00:34:32,030
Thanks, Xiaoman.

915
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:34,710
This Shanghai liquor

916
00:34:34,710 --> 00:34:37,570
just can't compare to
the Northeastern moonshine.

917
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:40,400
Look how high
your standards are, Yan. Seriously.

918
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:42,060
Just make do with it. Alright?

919
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:45,840
So many?

920
00:34:46,929 --> 00:34:47,560
It's done.

921
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:49,250
Great, it's done.

922
00:34:49,250 --> 00:34:51,449
The internet speed here is really fast.

923
00:34:52,630 --> 00:34:54,280
Growing up together—

924
00:34:54,550 --> 00:34:55,800
and they're still together now.

925
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:57,710
This must've been written in the stars.

926
00:34:57,710 --> 00:34:58,960
Xia Lei is a good kid.

927
00:34:59,630 --> 00:35:00,480
Tell him

928
00:35:00,510 --> 00:35:01,760
to come here for dinner

929
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:02,920
more often on weekends,

930
00:35:02,920 --> 00:35:04,500
and that he doesn't have to
stand on ceremony here.

931
00:35:04,500 --> 00:35:06,100
Okay, I'll tell him.

932
00:35:06,490 --> 00:35:08,940
I've liked Xia Lei since he was little.

933
00:35:09,030 --> 00:35:10,190
He's always loved to study.

934
00:35:10,190 --> 00:35:11,800
Look, as soon as he got here,

935
00:35:12,030 --> 00:35:14,070
he went straight to the computer.

936
00:35:14,590 --> 00:35:16,590
He's just single-mindedly
devoted to studying.

937
00:35:16,590 --> 00:35:17,440
I like that.

938
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:19,020
Look at you.

939
00:35:19,150 --> 00:35:20,750
You're implying something.

940
00:35:21,590 --> 00:35:22,590
Don't overthink it.

941
00:35:22,590 --> 00:35:23,590
Okay.

942
00:35:23,940 --> 00:35:25,800
By the way, I saw something called

943
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:27,110
a BBS earlier. Look.

944
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:28,320
What BBS?

945
00:35:28,370 --> 00:35:29,600
It talks a lot about

946
00:35:29,630 --> 00:35:30,710
art stuff.

947
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:32,400
I noticed the discussions in there
were quite intense.

948
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:34,400
I thought you might find it helpful.

949
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:41,560
Dongdong.

950
00:35:42,190 --> 00:35:43,840
How's your sawing coming along?

951
00:35:43,840 --> 00:35:45,320
-How come you still haven't finished yet?
-Xiaoman.

952
00:35:45,320 --> 00:35:46,960
The whole building is out of water
and waiting for this pipe.

953
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:47,820
Hurry up, okay?

954
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:48,620
Wait, wait.

955
00:35:48,800 --> 00:35:50,190
We agreed before we came

956
00:35:50,320 --> 00:35:51,760
that my job would just be
lifting and carrying.

957
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:53,960
But look at me now—sawing,

958
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:55,190
then I'll have to do the installing.

959
00:35:55,190 --> 00:35:57,190
Do you expect me to do all this work
by myself?

960
00:35:57,190 --> 00:35:58,400
What work have you done?
You've only been sawing pipes.

961
00:35:58,400 --> 00:35:59,400
I've been busy up there for so long.

962
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:00,190
What have you done?

963
00:36:00,190 --> 00:36:01,920
Hey, y-you can't just focus on...

964
00:36:01,920 --> 00:36:03,850
I-I've still got 4 more pipes here.

965
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:05,400
I can't possibly get it done that fast.

966
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:07,460
This isn't an electric saw, you know?

967
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:08,590
Do you still want to eat meat or not?

968
00:36:08,590 --> 00:36:08,960
I do.

969
00:36:09,630 --> 00:36:10,840
Do you still want to buy popcorn or not?

970
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:11,320
I do.

971
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:12,630
Then just hurry up and do your work.

972
00:36:12,630 --> 00:36:13,320
Yeah, I'm on it. I'm on it.

973
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:15,000
If you keep dawdling, I'll dock your pay.

974
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:16,060
You can dock my pay,

975
00:36:16,670 --> 00:36:18,690
but before you do that, don't you think

976
00:36:18,690 --> 00:36:19,920
you should give me my pay first?

977
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:21,290
I haven't seen a dime all day—

978
00:36:21,290 --> 00:36:22,290
only a few drinks.

979
00:36:22,330 --> 00:36:23,400
So your happiness counts,

980
00:36:23,400 --> 00:36:25,000
and mine counts for nothing?

981
00:36:25,190 --> 00:36:26,030
Are you stupid?

982
00:36:26,030 --> 00:36:28,320
Who pays you
when the job is only half done?

983
00:36:28,320 --> 00:36:29,120
Who does that?

984
00:36:29,510 --> 00:36:31,030
I've been working since this morning.
Look what time it is now.

985
00:36:31,030 --> 00:36:31,590
I don't care what time it is.

986
00:36:31,590 --> 00:36:32,210
Even if it takes until next year,

987
00:36:32,210 --> 00:36:34,150
you won't get paid until you finish.

988
00:36:34,150 --> 00:36:36,840
-Just hurry up, okay?
-♪ We workers have the power ♪

989
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:38,370
♪ We workers have the power ♪

990
00:36:38,550 --> 00:36:40,410
Look at all this dilly-dallying.

991
00:36:41,150 --> 00:36:42,400
Anything with a stick,

992
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:44,320
a pipe, or running water,

993
00:36:44,350 --> 00:36:46,150
we've basically fixed them all.

994
00:36:46,590 --> 00:36:48,880
But we've only done one household
in all these days.

995
00:36:48,880 --> 00:36:50,110
At this rate,

996
00:36:50,510 --> 00:36:51,920
forget about going to Shanghai—

997
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:53,310
you'll struggle to
even get past Shanhaiguan.

998
00:36:53,310 --> 00:36:56,030
Lulu and I might also end up breaking up
because of this.

999
00:36:56,030 --> 00:36:58,510
I've thought about this carefully.

1000
00:36:59,230 --> 00:37:00,150
In our plant,

1001
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:02,200
most people started as workers.

1002
00:37:02,590 --> 00:37:04,800
They don't need to hire anyone
for this kind of work.

1003
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:06,590
They can do it themselves, right?

1004
00:37:06,590 --> 00:37:08,840
We're just practicing in our plant now.

1005
00:37:09,190 --> 00:37:10,320
My ultimate goal

1006
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:11,960
is to expand our business

1007
00:37:12,360 --> 00:37:13,800
to Tiecheng.

1008
00:37:13,860 --> 00:37:15,260
There's more work there.

1009
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:18,400
Tiecheng? Better stay in our plant.

1010
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:20,910
Competition is so fierce nowadays,
you know?

1011
00:37:20,910 --> 00:37:21,930
I'm putting it here, Madam.

1012
00:37:21,930 --> 00:37:24,330
Even sweet potato vendors fight over turf.

1013
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:26,630
Nonsense.

1014
00:37:26,630 --> 00:37:29,590
We are skilled workers, you know?

1015
00:37:30,550 --> 00:37:32,320
We can't be rough like that.

1016
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:35,000
If we do this job well

1017
00:37:35,030 --> 00:37:36,630
and ensure top quality,

1018
00:37:36,630 --> 00:37:39,630
we'll definitely have plenty of money
and work there.

1019
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:41,800
Then go if you want.

1020
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:44,360
I'm going to see monkeys with Lulu
this afternoon.

1021
00:37:44,360 --> 00:37:45,160
What monkeys?

1022
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:48,380
In our park, the one nearby,

1023
00:37:48,590 --> 00:37:49,880
there's a monkey show.

1024
00:37:51,400 --> 00:37:53,200
Lulu really has a thing for that.

1025
00:37:53,510 --> 00:37:55,960
She's with you every day
and still wants to see a monkey show?

1026
00:37:55,960 --> 00:37:57,760
Is that show any better than you?

1027
00:38:31,590 --> 00:38:32,590
You're auditing the class here,

1028
00:38:32,590 --> 00:38:35,250
so stop eating something
that smells so strong.

1029
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:41,360
Almost there.

1030
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:48,000
Mr. Fan.

1031
00:38:48,190 --> 00:38:49,590
You're in the computer business now?

1032
00:38:49,590 --> 00:38:50,320
You're here.

1033
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:53,800
What do you think? Awesome, right?

1034
00:38:53,800 --> 00:38:56,000
I bought these two
from students returning from abroad.

1035
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:57,200
They're so new.

1036
00:38:57,590 --> 00:38:59,520
It... It'll be a shame to sell them.

1037
00:38:59,790 --> 00:39:01,790
Model 486. See if you like it.

1038
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:04,000
If you do, take one.

1039
00:39:05,190 --> 00:39:06,190
I do,

1040
00:39:06,630 --> 00:39:08,360
but I can't afford it. Let's go.

1041
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:09,970
As Communication Engineering majors,

1042
00:39:09,970 --> 00:39:12,030
isn't it weird to not have computers?

1043
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:12,960
It is.

1044
00:39:13,150 --> 00:39:14,320
None of us have computers.

1045
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:15,450
So we have to buy one.

1046
00:39:15,760 --> 00:39:16,960
Look how nice this is.

1047
00:39:20,190 --> 00:39:20,990
How much is it?

1048
00:39:21,190 --> 00:39:22,790
Don't talk to me about money.

1049
00:39:22,920 --> 00:39:25,230
How vulgar. If you like it, just take one.

1050
00:39:25,450 --> 00:39:26,340
Take one?

1051
00:39:26,630 --> 00:39:28,300
Even if you gave it to me for free,
I couldn't take it.

1052
00:39:28,300 --> 00:39:29,650
Wait... If you give it to me,
I'll take it.

1053
00:39:29,650 --> 00:39:30,400
No, no, no.

1054
00:39:30,440 --> 00:39:31,510
I didn't mean for free.

1055
00:39:31,510 --> 00:39:34,280
I meant
however much I paid for this computer

1056
00:39:34,420 --> 00:39:35,590
is how much I'll sell it to you for.

1057
00:39:35,590 --> 00:39:38,250
That's still too expensive.
We can't afford it.

1058
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:41,190
I can see you don't know much about
national affairs.

1059
00:39:41,190 --> 00:39:42,630
Nowadays, people can get a mortgage

1060
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:44,560
from the bank to buy a house.

1061
00:39:44,590 --> 00:39:45,760
The same goes for this computer.

1062
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:47,070
You can pay for it in installments.

1063
00:39:47,070 --> 00:39:49,630
I'm sure you can pay it off
within your 4 years of college.

1064
00:39:49,630 --> 00:39:51,630
Yes or no? Give me a straight answer.

1065
00:39:51,630 --> 00:39:52,560
Yes. We want one.

1066
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:53,630
Why are you saying yes?

1067
00:39:53,630 --> 00:39:55,630
You don't even know how much it is...

1068
00:39:55,640 --> 00:39:56,400
Great deal, isn't it?

1069
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:58,000
Senior Fan has already given us his word.

1070
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,590
Just grant me this wish, okay?

1071
00:39:59,590 --> 00:40:00,840
How about we split it?

1072
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:02,190
You and I can
pay the installments together.

1073
00:40:02,190 --> 00:40:02,990
It's settled.

1074
00:40:03,240 --> 00:40:04,570
Senior Fan, we want one.

1075
00:40:04,590 --> 00:40:05,050
Move it.

1076
00:40:05,190 --> 00:40:05,650
Move it.

1077
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:07,190
Look at Eight's attitude.

1078
00:40:07,190 --> 00:40:08,400
What do you mean move it...

1079
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:09,480
Shut up and move it.

1080
00:40:14,250 --> 00:40:14,730
What...

1081
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:16,630
What the heck?

1082
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:20,680
W-Where is the leak coming from?

1083
00:40:21,030 --> 00:40:22,030
The second floor!

1084
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:24,550
Didn't you tighten the valve?

1085
00:40:24,550 --> 00:40:25,670
I-I don't know!

1086
00:40:26,070 --> 00:40:28,280
It's leaking!
Water is flowing into the hallway!

1087
00:40:28,280 --> 00:40:29,140
We're done for.

1088
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:30,280
We're done for.

1089
00:40:30,280 --> 00:40:30,840
The master valve...

1090
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:32,440
Where's the master valve, Sis?

1091
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:33,070
Where's the master valve?

1092
00:40:33,070 --> 00:40:34,400
You have to find
the safety master valve first and...

1093
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:34,920
Mr. Ding...

1094
00:40:34,920 --> 00:40:36,720
Hurry up and notify that family.

1095
00:40:36,730 --> 00:40:38,000
Their house has been flooded. Quick.

1096
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,360
Xiaoman, your skills are truly amazing.

1097
00:40:39,360 --> 00:40:40,470
Look at all this flood—

1098
00:40:40,470 --> 00:40:41,400
Saying that at a time like this, huh?

1099
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:42,030
Hurry up!

1100
00:40:42,280 --> 00:40:43,140
Come up with me.

1101
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:44,860
But Mr. Ding, he's the one
who caused the leak!

1102
00:40:44,860 --> 00:40:46,000
Why did you hit me again?

1103
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:46,760
Hurry up and n-notify...

1104
00:40:46,760 --> 00:40:48,070
Notify that family on the first floor,

1105
00:40:48,070 --> 00:40:48,670
Dongdong.

1106
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:50,680
It's over. It's all over.

1107
00:40:50,920 --> 00:40:51,510
So over.

1108
00:40:59,070 --> 00:41:01,320
Hey, everyone, stop for a second.

1109
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:05,070
Let me

1110
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:07,770
reintroduce these two classmates to you.

1111
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:11,210
One is Nezha, who wreaked havoc
in the Dragon Palace.

1112
00:41:11,440 --> 00:41:14,370
The other is Monkey King
from the Water Curtain Cave.

1113
00:41:15,150 --> 00:41:16,440
These two classmates,

1114
00:41:16,670 --> 00:41:18,150
thinking their skills were up to par,

1115
00:41:18,150 --> 00:41:19,150
went out to work.

1116
00:41:20,280 --> 00:41:22,840
You didn't even check the water pressure

1117
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:24,620
before starting work?

1118
00:41:24,630 --> 00:41:27,960
Don't you know that
residential buildings use water pumps?

1119
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:29,880
They just turned on the valve

1120
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:31,480
after connecting the pipes.

1121
00:41:32,020 --> 00:41:33,840
All the water pipes in that hallway burst.

1122
00:41:33,840 --> 00:41:36,500
Now it really has become
the Water Curtain Cave.

1123
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:40,720
How did those people
even dare to hire them?

1124
00:41:41,190 --> 00:41:42,440
Why wouldn't they?

1125
00:41:42,440 --> 00:41:44,070
We showed them our student IDs.

1126
00:41:44,070 --> 00:41:45,670
We're professionally trained.

1127
00:41:45,670 --> 00:41:46,760
Give it a rest, will you?

1128
00:41:46,760 --> 00:41:48,290
You still dare to talk back?

1129
00:41:48,550 --> 00:41:49,280
Very well.

1130
00:41:50,070 --> 00:41:53,070
They're the top students
of our technical school now.

1131
00:41:53,280 --> 00:41:54,940
The whole city knows about it.

1132
00:41:56,190 --> 00:41:58,230
If Mr. Ding hadn't acted fast,

1133
00:41:58,920 --> 00:42:01,650
the consequences
would have been unimaginable.

1134
00:42:02,230 --> 00:42:04,920
Mr. Ding is always
cleaning up your messes.

1135
00:42:05,180 --> 00:42:06,380
He's a Grade 8 turner,

1136
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:09,100
yet he had to go door to door
to apologize for you.

1137
00:42:12,070 --> 00:42:14,710
Mr. Ding... He cleaned up our mess again?

1138
00:42:16,470 --> 00:42:18,000
With the shoddy work you do,

1139
00:42:18,840 --> 00:42:21,040
you definitely didn't wrap enough hemp

1140
00:42:21,330 --> 00:42:23,060
and didn't tighten the faucet.

1141
00:42:23,150 --> 00:42:23,760
Also,

1142
00:42:23,760 --> 00:42:25,420
the bend must have be clogged.

1143
00:42:26,880 --> 00:42:28,140
If Mr. Ding hadn't been

1144
00:42:28,190 --> 00:42:30,150
checking your work right behind you,

1145
00:42:30,150 --> 00:42:32,610
how could you have earned money
that easily?

1146
00:42:35,280 --> 00:42:37,400
Remember this. This is a lesson.

1147
00:42:38,230 --> 00:42:39,400
If your technique isn't good enough,

1148
00:42:39,400 --> 00:42:40,660
nothing else matters;

1149
00:42:41,150 --> 00:42:42,880
if your skills aren't up to par,

1150
00:42:43,670 --> 00:42:44,600
you're nothing.

1151
00:42:46,150 --> 00:42:47,550
Continue with the class!

1152
00:42:54,190 --> 00:42:56,190
Well, I just didn't fix it right,
so the pipe burst.
